body:
Given the following code ([playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=31f869a69a49ec509e95f6a7509f3ba5)):

```rust
struct S;

trait Id {
    fn id(&self) -> &Self {
        self
    }
}

impl Id for S {}

fn main() {
    let _i : &dyn Id = &S;
}
```

The current output is:

```
error[E0038]: the trait `Id` cannot be made into an object
  --> src/main.rs:12:24
   |
12 |     let _i : &dyn Id = &S;
   |                        ^^ `Id` cannot be made into an object
   |
note: for a trait to be "object safe" it needs to allow building a vtable to allow the call to be resolvable dynamically; for more information visit <https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/items/traits.html#object-safety>
  --> src/main.rs:4:21
   |
3  | trait Id {
   |       -- this trait cannot be made into an object...
4  |     fn id(&self) -> &Self {
   |                     ^^^^^ ...because method `id` references the `Self` type in its return type
   = help: consider moving `id` to another trait
   = note: required for `&S` to implement `CoerceUnsized<&dyn Id>`
   = note: required by cast to type `&dyn Id`

error[E0038]: the trait `Id` cannot be made into an object
  --> src/main.rs:12:14
   |
12 |     let _i : &dyn Id = &S;
   |              ^^^^^^^ `Id` cannot be made into an object
   |
note: for a trait to be "object safe" it needs to allow building a vtable to allow the call to be resolvable dynamically; for more information visit <https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/items/traits.html#object-safety>
  --> src/main.rs:4:21
   |
3  | trait Id {
   |       -- this trait cannot be made into an object...
4  |     fn id(&self) -> &Self {
   |                     ^^^^^ ...because method `id` references the `Self` type in its return type
   = help: consider moving `id` to another trait
```

Showing E0038 once should be sufficient for this code.
